reviews.review:
Coming from Dbd Ps4 first and only a player for just under 2 years, I really appreciate the full breath of this game through PC. Its a crazy love hate fun run of trying to stay alive and relying on your friends or strangers to make it out while dealing with pulse pounding skill checks and that awful chase sequence. While there's always your fair share of trolls or toxic players its hard to find something I don't really enjoy about this game. From my personal standpoint I've never encountered real hot heads aside from the occasional "WhY dID yOu Go In tHe BaSeMeNt". The devs of Dbd update the game consistently and often listen to all feedback players have to say about it. If there's glitches or bugs they'll swoop in and fix them almost immediately. Their twitter page is also an easy way to keep up to date on the happenings of the game as well as what the latest bugs/glitches are that they're addressing. In light of recent games switching to a 'battle pass' type loot table, dbd created it's own version and while it's similar it's also not. They made it their own and really I'm cool with it. 

Pros;
Devs THAT LISTEN
Evolving gameplay with current trends
Many MANY different perk combinations for the most unpredictable gameplay
They nod at the 13th for rank reset (hehe)

Cons;
idk, some people suck sometimes? 
so many skins;;;; 
some glitches are absolute trash and you will unfortunately de-rank if you can't continue playing
